n": []}, {"name": "pynxos.device.Device.facts", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a dictionary of facts about the device.\n\nThe dictionary must include the following keys.\nAll keys are strings, the value type is given in parenthesis:\n    uptime (int)\n    vendor (str)\n    os_version (str)\n    interfaces (list of strings)\n    hostname (str)\n    fqdn (str)\n    uptime_string (str)\n    serial_number (str)\n    model (str)\n    vlans (list of strings)\n\nThe dictionary can also include a vendor-specific dictionary, with the\ndevice type as a key in the outer dictionary.\n\nExample:\n    {\n        \"uptime\": 1819711,\n        \"vendor\": \"cisco\",\n        \"os_version\": \"7.0(3)I2(1)\",\n        \"interfaces\": [\n            \"mgmt0\",\n            \"Ethernet1/1\",\n            \"Ethernet1/2\",\n            \"Ethernet1/3\",\n            \"Ethernet1/4\",\n            \"Ethernet1/5\",\n            \"Ethernet1/6\",\n        ],\n        \"hostname\": \"n9k1\",\n        \"fqdn\": \"N/A\",\n        \"uptime_string\": \"21:01:28:31\",\n        \"serial_number\": \"SAL1819S6LU\",\n        \"model\": \"Nexus9000 C9396PX Chassis\",\n        \"vlans\": [\n            \"1\",\n            \"2\",\n            \"3\",\n        ]\n    }"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}]}